# Feature Implementation for Evaluation

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The AI Agent requires an LLM. Since this needs to be completed for tomorrow's evaluation, I suggest implementing a **simple Mock AI Agent** endpoint that acts as an insurance assistant (fast and guaranteed not to break due to API limits/keys), OR if you have an OpenAI/Gemini API key, we can integrate the real API. Let me know your preference when approving this plan!
> Also, I will outline VPS deployment using standard [docker-compose.yml](file:///home/dhruv/sem4/DBMS/EnsureVault/docker-compose.yml), which is production-ready for this scale.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Accounts & Roles
I will create a new SQL initialization script to automatically provision the required database profiles when Docker starts.
#### [NEW] [v3_roles_and_users.sql](file:///home/dhruv/sem4/DBMS/EnsureVault/backend/sql/v3_roles_and_users.sql)
- Creates `dba_admin` with `ALL PRIVILEGES` and `GRANT OPTION`.
- Creates `data_analyst` with only `SELECT` (view only) on `ensurevault.*`.
- Creates `claims_processor` with `SELECT`, `UPDATE` on specific tables (no create permissions).

---

### AI Agent Backend
Add a new Chatbot API endpoint to simulate an intelligent assistant dealing with insurance workflows.
#### [MODIFY] [backend/src/main.py](file:///home/dhruv/sem4/DBMS/EnsureVault/backend/src/main.py)
- Include the new chat router.
#### [NEW] [backend/src/routers/ai.py](file:///home/dhruv/sem4/DBMS/EnsureVault/backend/src/routers/ai.py)
- `POST /api/v1/chat` endpoint holding the agent's logic (mocked or querying a real LLM based on your preference).

